gomodel:SYNGO_1023  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The paper uses immunogold-silver detection to study the subcellular localization of WLS in noradrenergic locus coeruleus neurons. Wls is a multi-pass transmembrane glycoprotein essential for Wnt cell signaling.\n\nFigure 3 shows silver deposits in somatodendritic processes apposing a presynaptic, vesicle-filled terminal. Some deposits are associated with the plasma membrane. Since that a clear association with sub cellular organelles is not seen or mentioned, and the membrane association is not directly at the postsynaptic membrane, one can (only) use the above-mentioned data to demonstrate a post-synaptic localization of Wls.. Experimental description: 'Twelve adult male Sprague-Dawley rats (Harlan Sprague Dawley Inc., Indianapolis, IN, USA; 250-270g) housed two to three to a cage (20°C, 12-h light, 12-h dark cycle lights on 0700) were used in this study.'" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" ;
        dc:date           "2017-08-17" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1023" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

